# Environment variables this project actually reads. Copy to .env (gitignored) or set
# them in your shell/session; nothing here is required for the test suite to pass.
#
# NOTE: API credentials for this project do NOT live in environment variables. They are
# read from gitignored YAML/JSON under config/ - see config/credentials.example.yaml,
# config/tradier.example.yaml and config/telegram.example.json. The variables below are
# the complete set of env vars referenced anywhere in the tree.

# --- alerting -------------------------------------------------------------
# Gmail app password used by scripts/alert_watch.py for SMTP email alerts.
# The variable NAME is configurable via config/alerts.json -> email.smtp_pass_env.
# Read at: scripts/alert_watch.py (os.environ.get(...)). Unset -> email alerts skip.
ATLAS_ALERT_SMTP_PASS=your-16-char-gmail-app-password-here

# --- telegram failsafe bot (documented by config/telegram.example.json) -----
# These override config/telegram.local.json for the equity-era failsafe bot. The bot
# script itself is NOT part of this tree any more (archived with the equity system), so
# nothing currently reads them; they are listed only because the shipped example config
# still names them.
# ATLAS_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=your-telegram-bot-token-here
# ATLAS_TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=your-numeric-telegram-chat-id-here

# --- local-model time gate (optional) -------------------------------------
# Absolute path to the shared localgate script that decides whether local-LLM work may
# run right now (exit 0 = allowed). Read at: scripts/run_overnight_lab.py,
# scripts/tag_catalyst_headlines.py. Unset/missing -> those LLM stages fail CLOSED.
ATLAS_LOCALGATE=C:\path\to\localgate.py

# --- interpreter ----------------------------------------------------------
# The runners and tests import the repo root as a package root. conftest.py handles this
# for pytest; the launch scripts set it explicitly for direct script invocation.
PYTHONPATH=.
